name: The LGBT Center
directions: Right in the back, labelled "All-Gender Bathroom"
comment: This is an LGBTQ+ center, you are welcome here

name: Life Alive Urban Oasis
directions: Back of restaurant. Two one-toilet restrooms with no gender designation.
comment: You need to be a paying customer, however, the staff there are unlikely to turn you down if you're comfortable saying you need a gender-neutral bathroom.

name: Health Net of West Michigan
comment: Staff is very friendly, ask for directions to the bathroom. If there are meetings going on (rare), they may need to escort you through a secured staff area.

name: South Seattle College
directions: There's one in the automotive Building, the Nobel Chan education center and cascade court

name: Maucker Union
directions: In the corner between Essentials and pizza place.

name: Legal Action Center
comment: You have to be on the security list to get into the building. But if you have an appointment with any of the businesses in the building (at least on the fourth floor but probably other floors too) you'll be able to use a single stall bathroom.

name: Woodfield Mall
directions: Upper level by JC Penny's. Bathroom is near the entrance of the South West entrance/exit hallway.
comment: Completely open to the public during mall hours.

name: Bread Nolita Restaurant
directions: In basement. Stairs or elevator can be taken to use restrooms
comment: Restroom is for paying customers, exceptions sometimes made depending on circumstances.

name: IIT - Tech North
comment: Technically for IIT students, but you don't need an ID to get in if coming in through the North entrance.

name: IIT - Hermann Hall
directions: First floor, in the southwest corner.
comment: Technically for IIT students, but you don't need an ID to get in.

name: Keefe Campus Center, Amherst College
directions:
Basement - past vending machines, take a right, it's on the right
2nd floor - next to the elevator

name: Petsmart
directions: In the back left corner of store

name: Cupcake Royale
comment: There's two bathrooms, both unisex. You need to get a key from the counter. They're hanging from hooks at the end of the counter, and you don't really need to ask.

name: Vons
directions: At the back of the store behind the produce section.

name: Career Edge
directions: In through the door; to the right there will be a large desk in the middle of the room. Go past the desk until the Jobs Wanted posters are on your right, and it will be on the left.
comment: Staff are extremely nice; feel free to ask for directions if you're not clear.

name: Cooperage Wine & Whiskey Bar
directions: The bar is inside the Curtis Center, on the 7th Street side. There are 2 single-stall restrooms, and they are in the back of the bar.

name: Garage Bar
directions: Straight back from the front door, into back dining room, on the left.
comment: There are two large, gender neutral restrooms, with great paper towels. :)

name: Yale University Yale Repertory Theatre
directions: Basement lounge on the right past the concessions bar.
comment: Only open when shows are running.

name: Yale University Yale Repertory Theatre
directions: First floor to right of entrance.
comment: Only open when shows are running.

name: University of Oregon, HEDCO Building
directions: Second floor, outside office suite 240
comment: Open building hours 8-5

name: Centurian/Transformation
directions: Through foyer, turn right into hallway, left down next hallway.
comment: We do not have outdoor signage because this is office administration space, but our company has served the LGBT, trans, and kink community since 1969. Just come on in and ask to use the restroom :-)

name: Penn State University Libraries, Pattee and Paterno Library
directions: First floor central Pattee, by central staircase.
comment: Labeled as a family bathroom. It's safe to ask where it is at any of the welcome desks.

name: Ballard Public Library
directions: Ask at the information desk for the family restroom to be unlocked

name: University at Buffalo School of Law
directions: Single stall gender neutral  bathrooms. Accessible on 5th and 7th floors. All bathrooms in the law library are also single-stall, may be too small to accommodate wheelchairs.

name: CREAM
comment: Code needed, available from shop keepers next door.

name: Starbucks
comment: Token required, ask for one from the barista.

name: Zeal
comment: Two gender neutral restrooms. I believe must be a customer to use, can purchase a cheap juice product.

name: Brass Tacks
directions: 2 gender-neutral single-stall restrooms

name: University of Oregon Erb Memorial Union
directions: first floor, south wing, near the entrance.
comment: All Gender multiple stall restroom.

name: University of Oregon Health Center
directions: First floor of the Health Center.
comment: Open during regular business hours.

name: Florida International University Allied Health Complex Building 5
directions: Room Numbers: AHC 303, 304, 403, 404, 503 & 504; Next to conference rooms on the Northeast side of building.
comment: The third fourth and fifth floor of this building are mirrored, so with two restrooms on each floor this building has a total of six.

name: Florida International University Stocker Astroscience Center
directions: Room Numbers: 207, 208, 307 & 308. Across from the elevator as you enter through the north side of the building.
comment: 4 restrooms with two on the second floor and 2 on the third floor.

name: Florida International University Lakeview Halls (North & South)
directions: Room Number: LH 106; When you walk in go straight and take the first right, Bathroom is right next to elevators and across from Mailboxes
comment: Only accessible to resident students, though you can probably find a student that will let you into the resident halls to use the restrooms. Lakeview has a North building and South building, but they are mirrors of each other so directions are the same.

name: Florida International University Student Health Center
directions: Room Number: SHC 184; Right when you walk in to the left of the elevator on the first floor.
comment: Only accessible during student health center building hours.

name: Florida International University Viertes Haus
directions: Room Number: VH 222; Second floor in the Communication Arts Department Hallway. Accessible by elevator.

name: Florida International University Parking Garage 6 Tech Station
directions: Room Number: PG6 139; Towards the back of the lounge in the center part of the building on the first floor.

name: Florida International University Parking Garage 5 Market Station
directions: Room Number: PG5 148; Past food court in the back of the building, take a left and go past the gendered public restrooms. If you get to the classroom area you've gone too far.

name: Florida International University Parkview Hall
directions: Next to Room 114 in East Lobby and Next to Room 152 in West Lobby
comment: Available to resident students only, though you can probably find a friendly person to let you into the residence halls. Parkview has two separate lobbies with separate entrances and both have gender neutral restrooms.

name: Florida International University Recreation Center
directions: Room Number: RC 222; Alongside the classroom area on the second floor, elevator accessible.
comment: Must have FIU student ID to sign into the Recreation Center

name: Florida International University School of International and Public Affairs
directions: Room Number: SIPA 107; Across from Auditorium in Hallway at the foot of the stairs

name: Patricia and Phillip Frost Art Museum
directions: Room Numbers: PPFAM 201 & 301; Second and Third floors across from elevator
comment: Must use during Museum hours, free admission.

name: Florida International University Everglades Hall
directions: EH 142 & 143; Between Lounge & Laundry Areas on the first floor. Two separate gender neutral restrooms.
comment: For resident students, though you can probably get a friendly person to let you into the building.

name: Florida International University Graham Center
directions: Room Number: GC 161; In the foot court across from Alamazar.

name: Music Library, Wilson Library, University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill
directions: The Music Library is in the basement of UNC's Wilson Library. This restroom is located in the Music Library stacks (where all of the books are kept). Enter through the main door to the Music Library, walk past the circulation desk, and go in the first door past the desk to your right. In this room, turn to the left and follow signs for the stacks through another door (which usually remains shut, but has a sign). From there, turn right and find the restroom in the center of the stacks.
comment: Single-use facility, unisex. Lock the main door to the restroom, as the stalls themselves do not lock. There are two stalls: one urinal, one toilet. If asked if you would like help when entering the Music Library, say thank you and that you're just browsing. (You should also be able to freely say that you are looking for the restroom without any harassment, and should not be asked whether you are a UNC student. But better safe than sorry--!)

name: Mandarin Wong
directions: Two gender-neutral restrooms behind a door marked "restrooms"; walk straight back from the front door.

name: The Wedge Pizzeria
directions: There are two single toilet restrooms located to the right of the entrance.
comment: One does not have to walk past customers or staff to access these toilets.

name: Knockdown Center
comment: Two restrooms with many private stalls each. One door is marked Gender Neutral Restroom, the other is marked Gender Neutral Restroom (Urinals)

name: Valley City State University Allen Memorial Library
directions: 2nd Floor on the north end of the building

name: Hybrid Bar
directions: In the tikibar side. But the gendered stalls in the main side no one really cares what bathroom you use since it's an LGBT bar.

name: Pizza Hut
comment: Paying customers only

name: Pompeii's Pizza
comment: Must be a paying customer

name: Seven Slot Grill
comment: Paying customers only

name: First Parish in Needham, Unitarian Universalist
directions: in the upstairs hallway, or downstairs (where the daycare is) at the back left of the hallway.
comment: Building is open days for daycare, evenings for ballet school, and weekends for church activities.

name: Strawbery Banke Museum Education Center
directions: across the street from the museum's parking lot
comment: Not the visitor center, but across the street

name: Cheesecake factory
directions: First left off of the entrance, by the other restrooms

name: Broadway Rose Theatre Company
directions: Gender neutral single stall bathroom available between two women's restrooms as well as in the Marquee Lounge (ask for access if not a Marquee Club Member)
comment: Facilities are only open during scheduled performances or events

name: Lovely, Too
directions: Head straight back once you enter; two unisex, accessible restrooms
comment: Coffee shop / bakery - not clear if you have to be a paying customer, but could probably get away with not buying anything as long as it's not completely empty

name: The Cleveland Institute of Art
directions: There are two single stall restrooms on the first floor next to the freight elevator

name: Walmart
directions: Single stall gender neutral in back by electronics

name: Culture and Society (CU) Building - FAU
directions: Second floor in the back. Near the Sociology Department.
comment: This is the building with the Living Room Theater. Near the corner of Brevard Ct. and Indian River St.

name: Culture and Society (CU) Building - FAU
directions: Third floor in the back. Near the Sociology Department.

name: University of Minnesota Institute of Child Development
directions: Second floor on the south side of the building, near room 115. Right next to the drinking fountain.
comment: Many stairs in this building but there is an elevator on the north side that can get you to the floor with the bathroom. Doors into the building have electric push buttons to open, but the door into the bathroom itself does not.

name: Westview High School
directions: Back of locker rooms, behind gym. The side that faces the swimming pool
comment: Students only, because, well, high school. This is just in case, for students at Westview who are not aware that there are gender neutral bathrooms on campus.

name: University of Puget Sound
directions: Located throughout campus, one for sure on first floor of Weyerhauser Hall (N 11th & Lawrence)

name: Roble Art Gym
directions: Walk into the main entrance, take the first right down a hallway and there are two bathrooms on the right

name: Peridance-Capezio Center
directions: One on ground floor, one on second floor. Ground floor bathroom is to left of entrance by staircase.

name: Pier Market Restaurant
comment: For Customers Only

name: Wipeout Bar and Grill
directions: Back left corner
comment: For customers only

name: Portland Loo @ General MacArthur Square
directions: North of Harvard Square proper, where Mass Ave splits around the bus tunnel. The Loo is on the traffic island opposite the cemetery, just a little north of the UU church.
comment: This is a "Portland Loo", a permanent outdoor restroom. It's semi-sheltered (rain, but not wind) and appears to be wheelchair-accessible. Changing table, automatic lighting, sit-down toilet, sink on outside (oddly enough). Exact location: 42.374932, -71.118924

name: Butch + Babes
comment: Very LGBTQ friendly bar + restaurant across from the queer youth center

name: St. Helens Public Library
directions: In the children's room (originally built as a family restroom), but you can still use it!
comment: In the children's room (originally built as a family restroom), but you can still use it!

name: First Parish In Needham
directions: One on each (of two) floors, though downstairs bathroom is behind locked doors (safety measure for daycare) during the week.
comment: Church office is typically open 9-2 M-F, with daycare and ballet keeping the building open later. Church usually closed Saturdays. Trans/genderqueer welcoming worship on Sundays at 10:30 am.

name: 21c Museum Hotel Durham
comment: These bathrooms are accessible 24/7. When you enter the bathroom, one wall to the bathroom is translucent. You need to lock the door in order for the wall to become opaque.

name: Moonraker Brewing
directions: In main entrance area of Moonraker Brewing
comment: Two single stall restrooms. One is accessible, one is not.

name: Target
directions: Directly to right of entrance, first door on right, it's labeled a "family restroom" but is free for single person use

name: Building Left of the Lot, Studio Classrooms
comment: Two restrooms.

name: San Francisco Street Bakery
directions: Go through the baking area to back of building.

name: Madison High School
directions: For students/visitors only - in the nurse's office in E hallway.
comment: Nurse is very nice and does not mind people coming in to use the restroom!

name: Fallowfield VIA rail station
directions: As soon as you come in the second set of doors to enter the main lobby. Directly to the left are vending machines and bathrooms. One is a family/unisex bathroom.
comment: Doesn't seem they care if you are using them if you are traveling or not. But there is always someone at thr front desk.

name: Shade Sunless Tanning Co
comment: By appointment business but welcome anytime it's open.

name: Goodwill
directions: Single stall, unlocked, gender specific restrooms are located at the back of the store on the left side.
comment: They are in a small hallway so are not very conspicuous. You do not have to be a paying customer.

name: Sunflower Vegetarian Cafe
directions: Doors on wall opposite food line.

name: Flatrock Coffee, Tea and More
directions: Past the coffee/food counter, around corner in back to the right.
comment: Have spoken with owners. Though the signs are for men's and women's rooms, they are ok with whomever using the restrooms.

name: Urban Environmental Lab
directions: There are a few single room restrooms to the right to the right of the front door.
comment: Typically the only people in the building are students or faculty, but no one will give you a hard time for coming in.

name: Shotgun Players
directions: In the lobby, adjacent to the "women's" restroom
comment: Shotgun's bathrooms are for theatre patrons and are open during the lobby hour before shows. If you are seeing a performance at Shotgun, there is a single-stall, lockable, all-genders bathroom in the lobby.
